text: Semenov-Tian-Shansky Peak (, ) is a mountain in the Kyrgyz Ala-Too Range of the Tian Shan. It is located in Ala Archa National Park in Kyrgyzstan. It is the tallest mountain in the Kyrgyz Ala-Too Range and is an Ultra with a prominence of 2231m.https://www.ukclimbing.com/logbook/crags/ala_archa_national_park-16529 The mountain is situated between the Ala-Archa River to the west and the Alamedin River to the east. == History == The peak is named for the Russian geographer Peter Semenov-Tian-Shansky. ==References== Category:Mountains of Kyrgyzstan Category:Chuy Region Category:Four-thousanders of the Tian Shan Category:Mountains of Ala Archa National Park
title: Semenov-Tian-Shansky Peak
